## 1. Minimal `thespub-req.ttl` (Requirements Register)

```ttl
PREFIX orcid:   <https://orcid.org/>
PREFIX rdf:     <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs:    <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX dcterms:     <http://purl.org/dc/terms/>
PREFIX prof:    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dx/prof/> 
PREFIX rdl:     <https://w3id.org/requirement-ontology/rdl/>
PREFIX skos:    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX req:     <https://w3id.org/requirement-ontology/rdl/>
PREFIX thespub: <http://test.linked.data.gov.au/def/thespub>
PREFIX thesreq: <http://test.linked.data.gov.au/def/thespub#>
PREFIX thesval: <http://test.linked.data.gov.au/def/thespub/validator>
PREFIX xsd:     <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX vocpub:  <https://linked.data.gov.au/def/vocpub>

#################################################################
#  ThesPub Profile (minimal starter)
#################################################################

thespub:
    a prof:Profile ;
    dcterms:title "ThesPub – Thesaurus-Friendly VocPub Extension Profile"@en ;
    prof:isProfileOf vocpub: ;
    prof:isProfileOf skos: ;
    prof:hasResource thesval: ;
    prof:hasToken "thespub" ;
    dcterms:creator orcid:0000-0001-5640-3202 ;
    dcterms:issued "2025-01-15"^^xsd:date .


#################################################################
#  Requirement THES-01 — One prefLabel per language
#################################################################

thesreq:THES-01
    a req:REQ_0011 ;  # Requirement
    skos:notation "THES-01" ;
    rdfs:label "At most one skos:prefLabel per language tag per concept"@en ;
    dcterms:description """
For any skos:Concept, there MUST NOT be more than one skos:prefLabel with the same language tag. This allows multilingual preferred labels (one per language) while preventing conflicting preferred labels within a single language.
"""@en .

#################################################################
#  Requirement THES-02 — Definition required for top concepts
#################################################################

thesreq:THES-02
    a req:REQ_0011 ;  # Requirement
    skos:notation "THES-02" ;
    rdfs:label "skos:definition is mandatory for top concepts"@en ;
    dcterms:description """
For thesaurus-style vocabularies, a skos:definition SHALL be provided for each skos:Concept where it is a top concept to add clarity. For any skos:Concept that is NOT a top concept, meaning may be
conveyed primarily via semantic relationships and placement in the concept network.
"""@en .

#################################################################
#  Requirement THES-03 — Consider at least one altLabel
#################################################################

thesreq:THES-03
    a req:REQ_0011 ;  # Requirement
    skos:notation "THES-03" ;
    rdfs:label "Consider at least one skos:altLabel per concept"@en ;
    dcterms:description """
For user-facing thesauri, each skos:Concept SHOULD have at least one skos:altLabel where appropriate, to support entry vocabulary and synonym search. This is a recommendation, not a strict constraint, and may be relaxed for very technical or tightly-controlled code lists.
"""@en .
```

